    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-21T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-21T10:00:00-05:00" n="907"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d907">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1133</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MIN1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-21T16:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 21, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 10.25 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1541. Minister of Foreign Affairs yesterday informed French Minister that as a
                    result of negotiations between Vorovski, Bolshevik representative here, Russian
                    soldiers, Red and White Guards, and the commander of Swedish expedition to the
                    Aland Islands, it had been agreed that all three groups would leave the islands
                    on Swedish ships on condition that Sweden would occupy islands with sufficient
                    force to protect population, who do not wish to take sides in present Finnish
                    struggle, but claim peace and protection. Swedish Government therefore decided
                    to send, and did send yesterday, additional expedition composed of one infantry
                    and one machine-gun company which with the force already there would amount to
                    about 500 men. Commander has instructions not to land his troops before the
                    three groups are ready to leave islands so as to avoid complications.</p>
                <p>Minister of Foreign Affairs added that he desired to inform French and British
                    Ministers of this, and to declare at the same time that this action was not to
                    be considered as the beginning of a permanent occupation as the Swedish
                    Government was still of the opinion that the Aland Islands question should be
                    solved by negotiations between England, France, and Finland and if these
                    negotiations led to no result, then at the peace conference.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MIN1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
